        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cli): harden Windows node pairing and approvals",
        "body": "## Summary\n- preserve stable Windows node/device identity across reconnects and same-key metadata refresh approvals, while still rotating unsafe/stale/revoked/mismatched device tokens\n- harden node pairing approval authz, pending/paired node presentation, and gateway node-event routing so Windows nodes are less likely to fall back to manual/TUI repair paths\n- route devices/nodes/gateway CLI RPC helpers through direct local gateway-client auth for explicit loopback shared token/password calls, without letting stale inactive env/config tokens suppress device-token fallback\n- make host-native Windows exec approval get/set payloads work through the dedicated `exec.approvals.node.*` gateway methods, including native payloads that omit `payloadJSON`\n- block raw `node.invoke systemExecApprovals.*` / `system.execApprovals.*` policy mutation paths and keep exec policy mutation on audited dedicated methods\n\n## Draft Snapshot\nCurrent pushed draft head: `882ed3f70885fd8e47a122f3b3e3b8ae15458d9f`.\n\nThis is pushed for review now. It is still draft because there is one accepted autoreview follow-up in the Control UI path and the broad changed gate is still blocked by the repo-wide oxlint backlog.\n\n## Proof On This Snapshot\n- `git diff --check` passed before commit.\n- Touched-file oxlint passed before commit: `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json $(git diff --name-only origin/main...HEAD -- '*.ts' '*.tsx')`.\n- Focused Windows-node/pairing/approval regression set passed before commit: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/call.test.ts src/cli/direct-loopback-gateway-auth.test.ts src/cli/gateway-rpc.runtime.test.ts src/cli/gateway-cli/call.test.ts src/cli/devices-cli.runtime.timeout.test.ts src/cli/devices-cli.test.ts src/cli/nodes-cli.coverage.test.ts src/cli/program.nodes-basic.e2e.test.ts src/gateway/server.node-invoke-approval-bypass.test.ts src/gateway/node-registry.test.ts src/gateway/node-command-policy.test.ts src/gateway/node-connect-reconcile.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/nodes.invoke-wake.test.ts src/infra/device-pairing.test.ts src/infra/node-pairing.test.ts src/tui/tui-command-handlers.test.ts` passed 6 Vitest shards / 402 tests.\n\n## Windows Node Pond Proof\n- Signed prerelease asset used: `OpenClawCompanion-Setup-x64.exe`, release `v0.6.0-alpha.14`, digest `sha256:36405bd72e2c11bae0aa051b551b339982a66ffb59820d977ad9983dbf0b4d98`.\n- Pond proof was run at `8ee11cb653c2b3cbbecbc2c3180d7bdbe3ea47f9`; the new pushed commit is lint/type-narrowing cleanup only and has not yet been rebuilt through the Azure pond.\n- Azure smoke passed with signed Windows nodes paired through the Linux gateway: paired=3, pending=0, connected=2; connected Windows nodes reported caps=7 and commands=20.\n- Feature smoke passed on a Windows node: `device.info`, `device.status`, `camera.list`, and `screen.snapshot`.\n- Exec approval smoke passed: `exec.approvals.node.get` returned enabled=true/default=deny/rules=22; raw `node.invoke system.execApprovals.get` was rejected; a temporary `echo *` allow rule was set via `exec.approvals.node.set`; `system.run` returned exit=0/stdout=`openclaw-clean`; policy restore returned to 22 rules/default deny; non-allowlisted command was denied by default policy.\n\n## Known Draft Items\n- Autoreview follow-up: Control UI still treats native Windows node exec approval snapshots as file-backed configs. It needs either native read-only rendering or native edit support before ready.\n- `GOMAXPROCS=2 CI=true OPENCLAW_TESTBOX=1 pnpm check:changed` still fails in `lint core` on unrelated repo-wide `typescript/no-unsafe-type-assertion` backlog. The touched-file lint for this branch is fixed.\n",
        "branch": "fix-windows-node-token-rotation",
